or 3), and only lumbar hematoma was associated with a good initial clinical 
neurological status (NG 0 or 1). Surgery was performed in 767 (80%) cases. 
Mortality was greater in patients older than 40 years of age (9%; p < 0.01). Sex 
did not influence any of these data (p > 0.05). CONCLUSIONS Factors that 
contribute to the formation of acute SEH are iatrogenic, not iatrogenic, or 
multifactorial. The treatment of choice is surgery, and the results of treatment 
are influenced by the patient's clinical and neurological status at admission, 
age, and the craniocaudal site.

